commentary: Mishra to Bravo, OUT caught at long-off and the West Indian cookie continues to crumble. Bravo had to play the big shot, because it's the Powerplay, but he picked out the region where Raina has a fielder in the deep. He came forward and lofted the ball straight to Harbhajan, didn't get to the pitch of the ball and got no power on the shot. Bravo didn't even attempt to run, just walked off as soon as he saw the ball head towards Harbhajan. What if he had been dropped?

Bravo didn't even attempt to run, just walked off as soon as he saw the ball head towards Harbhajan. What if he had been dropped?
